title: For Sale/Trade:  *** New ** RARE ** Wilkinson Linda *** Tactical 9mm Assault Pistol ** UZI / MAC 10 Style ***
postcontent:
This is a brand new Wilkinson Linda 9mm pistol. It comes complete with owners manual and all of the factory paperwork. This was one of the very hard to find late edition pistols with the threaded barrel to accept a sound suppressor or any other similar type of attachment.  I have owned several of these over the years and this has the nicest piece of wood I have ever seen on one. It also comes with 6 of the extremely well made and very hard to find 31 round factory magazines to provide a lifetime worth of shooting pleasure.
     The Wilkinson "Linda" was designed to be used as a tactical weapon for police SWAT and other special agencies. It was designed as an improved upgrade of the J&R 9mm carbine. Being a small company the founder Ray Wilkinson was obsessed with detail and quality control (he even named the pistol after his daughter), that the fit and finish need to be seen to be believed. Everything on this weapon is solid as a bank vault the bolt operates as smooth as silk! Unfortunately this unsurpassed quality control came at a price and it was hard to complete with the cheaper stamped competition from Ingram (Mac 10) and UZI. Not being able to compete on price forced Wilkinson out of business.
     It is very easy to disassemble and clean, due to the ingenious design of the firearm. Re-assembly is also simple due to the presence of the timed barrel, which ensures that the firearm will continue to perform with the same high degree of accuracy without the burden of re-sighting the gun each time that it is disassembled. In addition to being both attractive and accurate, the "Linda" has very little recoil which makes it a great target gun and very useful for home defense. Many of our customers have told us that it has become their favorite firearm. Additionally, because there were very few "Linda's" ever manufactured, they are destined to become collector's items.
     A full blow back semi-auto design, firing from a closed breech. The pre-ban “Linda” receiver is manufactured from T-16 aluminum [which is a high-grade aircraft aluminum] and is machined to very tight tolerances. Fully machined rather than die-cast or stamped metal and are not subjected to the flaws that are inherent in some other firearms that are currently being manufactured today. The trigger group is a reliably simple design with an excellent trigger pull, a nice balance for the firearm. The bolt assembly weighs [1 lb. 7 oz]. The front of the bolt extends well ahead of the breech and surrounding the rear of the barrel which prevents the barrel from free floating to provide better accuracy.
    The mags are sweated together and have several spot welds down the backs. The magazines are a double stack design, upon inspection of the disassembled magazine; there is a nice machined aluminum follower with a special rounded allen head bolt used as a bearing guide to help prevent binding during operation. You can see that there was a lot of thought put into the design of this magazine for reliability. The “Linda” is an attractive looking firearm and an accurate shooter, providing very tight target groupings. 

Please feel free to call or text with any questions. Thanks for looking REDACTED
